title: There are better products in the VEATOOL range.
review_text: I wanted to love these. I really did. I'd previously owned two sets of X08's, one failed (one earpiece broke), the other set's going strong. So I do appreciate the VEATOOL brand and their reliable/affordable set of products When I seen these, I thought 'oh this must be the next new thing'. Touch screen, etc. Lets start with some of the more obvious flaws. 1. Frequently disconnects - also very easy to de-pair with the other headset and give you that wonky out of phase audio feeling. 2. Charge lasts about an hour. Makes me think that something's constantly trying to pair or work harder than it needs to, to maintain a connection. I've disabled noise cancelling and graphic equalization. Still doesn't last longer. 3. The textured coating on the earpieces (while nice) can become quite slick and leave you fumbling and accidentally touch the controls on the earpiece when you didn't intend to , cutting off a call or other. 4. Touch screen on case. Nice idea but it is fiddly. Doesn't work well with big thumbs. If you want a basic but reliable model, try the X08. Good battery life, wireless charging and average noise cancelling. I will try other models in their lineup in the future, but I think these ones need some TLC from VEATOOL before they're ready for prime-time.

title: READ BEFORE PURCHASING
review_text: Don't believe the 5 star reviews!! This seller is dishonest and scamming people. They've submitted hundreds of AI generated reviews, giving their faulty/defective products 5 stars. I totally fell for it too. I didn't read any of the individual reviews before purchasing. I saw ‚Äúflash deal‚Äù $18.99 product usually worth (supposedly) $90, I saw a rating of 4.5 out of 1,400 reviews, and I read the summary of reviews generated by Walmart's AI bot, that said ‚Äúcustomers rave about this product and how amazing it is..‚Äù etc, etc, etc. So of course I thought I hit the jackpot by finding these ear buds at this price, so I immediately bought 2 pair. (One black case and one with a pink case) After receiving them, I was actually pleasantly surprised with the packaging and nice look and feel of the case and ear buds. I liked that it had a display screen to always show the battery level of the case and each ear bud. They were really easy to pair with my Apple TV. BUT- when I started watching my show while using them‚Ä¶ they were pausing and unpausing my show every few seconds, and completely disconnecting and reconnecting every 30 seconds or so. I'm not even exaggerating. It's so bad that these are completely unusable. I thought maybe the first pair was defective so I opened the second pair and they had the same issues. After all this, I decided to go read some of the hundreds of 5 star reviews. It was obvious that every single 5 star review is fake, AI generated reviews. All of the reviews and very similar in wording and length. Some of the reviews are just complete copies of other ones. All of the 5 star reviews are too perfect. Real people make typing errors, grammar and punctuation errors, spelling errors, and use abbreviations and/or slang. Just read thru a handful of them and you'll see what I mean. This seller should be banned from selling with Walmart. They are scammers and liars. I am embarrassed that I fell for it, but I'm hoping others will see this review and it can help prevent them from being scammed like I was.

title: HP Brought the Heat with this!
review_text: [This review was collected as part of a promotion.] This has to be, one of the best PC's I ever used, the combination of discrete components (fantastic processor, good RAM amount and speed, excellent storage, vibrant and clear display, excellent port availability, sound and built in tile capability). Beginning with packaging and a nod to sustainability, I love the simple cardboard recyclable box - I appreciate this more than having an elaborate and wasteful unboxing experience. Keep the cost lower, keep it simple - love it. The hardware itself has ocean-bound plastics and recycled aspects in it. Also, well done HP. This is exactly right - keep on this, we care! The power supply as a side note, had a great wrap around the cord - something that gave it a bit more personality and a nicer aesthetic. I appreciated this, though would never have expected it - but I like it! This originally had Windows 10 Pro on it, but upgraded to Windows 11 without issue swiftly with the updating process - my preference as well to be on 11. The machine is zippy, it handled multiple apps open, HD video playback and some intense computational tasks (lots of spreadsheet work) simultaneously - I did not notice any lag or the hardware skipping a beat. The keyboard is indeed quiet, much quieter than a few other large name brands I have, and the feel was soft to the touch. The trackpad was large, and responsive - sensitive almost and I had to dial it back a bit for my tastes (which are fully customizable). There is a built-in Tile feature, which I didn't seek out specifically, but it is interesting to have and has come in handy once already. Who knew, I would misplace my laptop. Camera quality is good, best in plenty of light - low light you can see the grain and artifacts pop up - so proper lighting setup applies here for those late night video calls or low-light conditions. Audio is bonkers. The B&O's do justice on web playback and streaming - really not bad for a laptop, and they grow on you for sure. The machine is a little heavier than I would have thought, not an issue, but I did notice it picking it up for the first time -it doesn't come to mind now but was one of those first impression items. The body is seems predominantly metal, durable and has held up - with some plastic (display case looks to be). Keyboard backlighting is good, helps in low light conditions as well but is not overbearing. I also enjoy having the fingerprint scanner - I'm not a fan of face recognition (which it can also do) so this is a great alternative for me. In all, its a very fast, powerhouse of a machine with very forward thinking capability. It will last me a considerable amount of time without replacement. Very happy with it, go HP on this one!

title: Incredible laptop!!
review_text: [This review was collected as part of a promotion.] After using this laptop for a few days I'm super impressed! It comes with options that I would want (i7 processor, 16GB of RAM, Nvida T550 GPU) and is crazy fast. It's not as common to have a dedicated GPU in most laptops now, but I highly recommend it if you'll be doing anything creative with photo/video/design/etc and this one does not disappoint. My biggest surprises so far are how much I like the fingerprint scanner (seriously, it makes logging in feel easier than unlocking my phone) and how great the screen is. Colors are fantastic, the display is very sharp, and the viewing angle has to be close to 180 degrees. I have a work laptop (different major brand) that is meant to be at a similar level but I didn't realize how disappointing the screen was until I started using this one. A slightly different approach with this laptop is to use 1920x1200 instead of 1920x1080. It feels the same which is good, but also gives more space vertically for all the toolbars at the top of programs which can take up way too much space on a laptop screen. I am also shocked at how good the speakers are, I love audio and have a fantastic home theater setup...which this doesn't compare to and I wouldn't expect it to. But I've never heard laptop speakers this good before where it's not painful to listen to music like it's in a tin can, these (separate right/left speakers) are enjoyable and can get plenty loud! I'm not sure how much of a difference the Wolf Pro Security will make but I guess time will tell. Having a Tile built in is a great idea and really enhances the physical security. It's slightly heavier than I was expecting but it's really not bad at all, it feels sturdy which I'd much rather have than something light and flimsy. The camera is sharp in bright light but pretty grainy in dim lighting (common on every laptop I've used), but I do appreciate the built-in camera cover that you can slide over.  The computer was quick to set up, connected flawlessly with my wireless HP printer in a few seconds, and it also connected right away with my dock (from a different brand) and could handle the laptop screen plus two other independent external monitors (I love USB-C docks and being able to connect everything with 1 cord including charging it). Speaking of cords, the power cord that comes with it is really cool, almost like a cloth feel instead of the usual plastic/rubber that every other laptop cord I've ever used has felt like...just a nice unexpected bonus! I work in software development, have had jobs in graphic design, video and photo editing, and worked in technical support/helpdesk environments for years so I'm pretty picky...but I can't say enough good things about this computer! I've used plenty of other brands in the last few years and hadn't really thought of HP as a major contender for a high-end laptop but this ZBook has absolutely changed my mind!

title: Never Again. (Will not remain powered off!)
review_text: Never again. Never another Lenovo. Good value but it has its quirks, which makes it quite unsuitable for travel. Even when powered fully off and with clamshell closed, laptop will turn itself back on! Don't know if it sits in sleep or hibernation but it does drain the battery! Useless. I expect when I fully power off a laptop for it to stay off! This apparently is a known problem for Lenovo laptops. (I normally have purchased ASUS machines). Also, I had an absolutely brilliant Dell machine with the same specs, at lower cost, and its battery would last 14-16 hours! (not just 4 as with this Lenovo).

title: Horrible syestem and service

I got the computer on affirm in which I'm still paying for. Had to call Affirm and they was asking me why Walmart wouldn't take my return. So Affirm is doing an investigation now. I cant do anything with this device and its useless to me.

The touchpad is so sensitive I have to use a mouse which is not a big deal but if I'm on the go makes it a challenge. It was easy to set up and does the bare minimum but if that's what you are looking for there are more affordable options out there. Very disappointed!

Windows update did not reinstall the drivers. I had to use a different computer to download a zip file with the Chuwi drivers, and then proceed to use the Tab, Space bar, and Enter keys to reinstall all drivers. I have not had to use this process of installing drivers since Windows XP. Once all drivers were installed, the laptop works great. It is very responsive and a great value for the price paid. title: Properly usable notebook PC
review_text: I've bought Chuwi PCs several times before, and I've always found their support to be very good, as long as you complain about any problems, they'll replace it right away. The first one I received did not have a functioning microphone (I checked with my voice recorder), so I had it replaced immediately. The first unit I received did not have a functioning microphone (confirmed by voice recorder), so I had it replaced immediately. It's not light, but not heavy either. It's not light, but it's not heavy either. Battery life is disappointing. However, it is usable. The most annoying problem is that the function keys cannot be used unless they are pressed simultaneously with the Fn key. This is a fatal flaw for Japanese input, and a big problem for work, so I emailed support (Aftersales), and in a few exchanges, they told me where to find the EF file and instructions. I managed to deal with the errors and unclear points in the instructions by myself, and in no time at all, it changed to the normal function key behavior. I really wonder why they don't make this the standard, even though the forum has a lot of complaints about the Fn key. Nevertheless, I'm very happy with the way it turned out.

I tried the Apple Store first, and one AirPod replacement was the same price as a brand new set!! We did a quick search and Walmart popped up. As always ordering was a painless simple process, and was delivered on time for Christmas. The AirPod arrived in decent packaging, bubble wrap and easy to read/comprehend, instructions. The AirPod was beyond clean, not a speck of dirt on it, and is in like new condition not marred or scratched at all. Took no time at all to connect to her original AirPod case and her phone, no issues whatsoever. My daughter was very pleased!!! Lastly, you can't beat the price for the quality of an expensive Apple product.

title: Great Sound and Comfort .
review_text: These headphones deliver very good sound quality with strong bass and clear calls. The noise cancellation works well, especially for this price range. They are comfortable to wear for long periods, and the battery life is impressive ‚Äî lasting as advertised. Recommend it!

title: Very Good value for the Price.
review_text: I recently picked up these Wireless Bluetooth Headphones and have been really impressed with their performance. The 5.4 Bluetooth connection is super stable, and the 40-hour battery life is an exaggeration,‚Äî It is more like 28 hours without needing to recharge. The three EQ modes are a nice touch, letting me switch between settings for music, calls, or just drowning out background noise. The four-mic ENC noise cancellation works well for calls; people on the other end say I sound clear even when I'm in a noisy environment. The bass boost is noticeable and adds a nice punch to music without sounding muddy. Comfort-wise, they fit nicely over the ears and don't cause fatigue even during long sessions. My only mild critique ‚Äî and the reason I'm holding back that fifth star ‚Äî is that the ear cups could be a bit more plush for extended wear. But overall, these are a solid choice for travel, home, or office use. Great value for the price!

title: Effortless Power %26 Organization
review_text: I've been using the Bluestone 3-in-1 Magnetic Wireless Charger for a few weeks now, and I couldn't be happier with the experience! This charger has truly transformed my daily routine by allowing me to power up my smartphone, Apple Watch, and AirPods all at once without the hassle of tangled cords. The sleek, ultra-thin folding design not only looks modern and stylish but also saves precious space on my desk and nightstand. The 15w super-fast charging for my phone is impressive, and knowing that it intelligently manages the charging speeds for my watch (2.5w) and AirPods (3.5w) gives me peace of mind. I love the magnetic closure and built-in kickstand, which add both functionality and a touch of sophistication to the unit. Plus, the non-slip base and overheat protection ensure that the charger remains safe and secure during use. The fact that it comes complete with a Type-C cable and a 20W PD charger is the icing on the cake. Whether I'm at home, in the office, or on the go, this charger is the ultimate accessory to keep all my essential devices powered and organized. I highly recommend it for anyone looking to simplify their tech setup without sacrificing performance!

title: So convenient, lightweight, and affordable!
review_text: I purchased the Bluestone 3-in-1 Charger for my husband, who travels frequently for work, and it has been a total game-changer for him. Before this, he was constantly packing (and misplacing) multiple charging cables for his phone, smartwatch, and earbuds. Now, with this all-in-one charger, he only needs to bring one device to charge everything, which has made his packing routine much more convenient. The ultra-thin folding design is perfect for travel‚Äîit folds compactly, takes up very little space in his bag, and even has a magnetic closure to keep it neatly folded. He also loves the built-in kickstand, which allows him to prop up his phone while it charges. The 15W super-fast wireless charging works efficiently, and he hasn't noticed any overheating issues, thanks to the overheat protection feature. Another big plus is that it comes with a Type-C cable and a 20W PD charger, so he didn't have to buy anything extra. The non-slip base ensures that it stays in place on his nightstand or hotel desk. Overall, this charger has been an excellent investment‚Äîit reduces clutter, keeps all his devices charged, and is perfect for travel or everyday use. Highly recommend!

title: Good gripping white noise
review_text: Thought we'd try this out for a top-bunk sleeper and it works great. The clamp actually gripped on the cylindrical-tubes of the bunk guard. Angle and speed easily adjustable and it has the right amount of ‚Äúwhite noise‚Äù to help with sleep. Hope it lasts!

I love this little fan! It's one of my fav purchases of the year. I use it every day, especially nights. As I need some air blowing on me while I sleep. Very low background noise. low space profile. It has two speeds. And there is a noticeable difference between them. They both give off good breeze and not an overpowered wind blow. The clip to hold the fan is big and it opens pretty wide as mentioned in the description. It was a concern as to where I would clip it before I ordered but it was for naught. Your table or edge will need at minimum a good 2 inch cleared length of edge if that is where you want to put it. The clip opens pretty wide too appropriately 3-4 inches. It opens wide and will require some hand strength. Once it's clipped on, it has the death grip on the edge or ledge. It will stay on unless you are fiddling around and pull it off. Yeah, I may have done that. It was totally user error tho. Not "cool breeze" fault. That's MY fan's name. Lol. Cool breeze gives a strong steady breeze. While white colored, not apparent collecting dust so far. However, all Fans will eventually do the dust collector thing. The fun part is that Cool breeze's head will and does tilt, swivel, flip, dip, dive and twirl to whatever direction your heart desires. Her wish is your command. She also has a twist knob so you can lock her into whatever configuration you want. This may be problematic for those with arthritis. The knob is small and in an awkward but convenient place. Again Her wish is your command. So, If you need a small breeze pointed on you or in your space and don't want a bulky fan sitting on your table or floor in your way, taking up valuable space, then this fan is for you. I don't think you will be disappointed. I am not and I was very skeptical. I am considering buying another for my laundry room. Enjoy.

title: Quiet, good clamp, lots of positions
review_text: Won't move a lot of air because, well, it's a small diameter fan. Moves enough for my use within a couple feet of cooled area. Quiet. Would prefer a rotary speed/off select than the slide switch. Like it can be pointed downward since it sits on an above shelf to blow downward. Does not oscillate, but I already knew that, and don't need it for where it is used. Would like the fan blade cage to be easier to separate for dusting (have to use a flat-blade screwdriver to pry the halves apart to get inside to dust the blades). I had one before, and this was a replacement. After near 4 years, the old one's motor bearing were getting noisy. Note: The fan blades are simply pressed onto the motor spindle, so friction holds the blades to the spindle. When pointed straight down, the blades will gradually slide off the spindle which will have the blades bang against the cage. Used hot-melt glue to affix blades to spindle. The clamp was sufficiently wide to handle affixing the fan to my headboard (which has a layer for the headboard, and another layer around the edges for decorative trim). This is very quiet which is needed for a fan near the head when sleeping in the bed. The slow speed is enough to cool me off when sleeping (to eliminate waking up sweaty). The head can rotate fore-aft and the stem can rotate 360 degrees, so it pretty much can be pointed in any direction.

title: Small train coming through
review_text: I received the box in the mail and noticed that it came from the return center. That's not a big deal. Returned items typically get put back into circulation. I opened it up. It was dirty. Whatever. I cleaned it off. It was easy to put together (one screw). I plugged it in and turned it on. Things started off well. It blows a good amount of air, sufficient for its size. It was quite soothing until a subtle little thump thump thumping started. And then it got louder. And louder. And louder. It seems the motor is vibrating inside the plastic caseing. Then another fun sound started. This one was a high pitched eeeeeeee that sounded somewhat metallic. I have no idea what that was about but that one was a deal breaker. It's going back to the store. Also, take notice that the padding inside of the clip is not thick enough to protect your furniture from the edges of the plastic.

review_text: The settings blow out nice cool air, even on low. I bought this for my mama to use by her bed at night as she has occasional hot flashes and this is much easier than getting up out of bed to turn on the ceiling fan, with this she can cut on and off and adjust as needed. I like the sturdiness of the stand, no worries with it falling back or over. It stays in place exactly how you adjust it. I also like how the power button is in the front. The one I have has the power in the back and have to turn it over to power on. With this option, makes it much easier to turn off and on while in bed and go right back to sleep üò¥ üí§! Also, the usb plug comes with the wall outlet plug and I have even used the usb plug without the wall plug, in my computer and the fan came right on! You can also use 4 AA batteries to use on the go. Not sure how long it would last on the batteries but definitely a good option to use if needed while out and about. For $14, this is definitely more than what we expected and hope it lasts a good long while. The only thing I dont like is that sometimes the power cord comes out just slightly, just barely out of the socket so you have to make sure it is all the way pushed in or else it will not power on. The first time using, we thought it was malfunctioning, but since we discovered that it has to be all the way in, I mean like no space whatsoever in between lol, it comes right on!

Rayovac AA batteries will not fit! I taped cover to hold down but 1 battery leaked, end broke creating hot outside compartment cover! (great value did but only lasted 6 hrs)I didnt try usb plug in. It did keep blowing air in sun porch where ppl smoke to keep from staying still in air, humid weather. As the batteries are dying remember the control button will only work on 2 then 1 then out!

I was looking for a small fan to put on my bedside for white noise. This fan has a light where the button is I didn't care for that and the sound of the fan was not what I was looking for I will be returning item.

title: On-the-Go Folding Fan
review_text: This mini folding fan can best be described as small but mighty. At less than 8 inches tall, it is ideal for use at a desk or table. It has a powerful air flow in 3 different speeds. This fan can also be hung using the attached folding handles. There are two sources of power: 4 AA batteries or the included USB cord and adapter. An added feature is the lighted power button.

title: Perfect for Travel
review_text: The Mainstays On-The-Go Folding Fan in white has many great features. The folding handle is also the stand and the hanger. So you can carry it, hang it or stand it. The Mainstays On-The-Go Folding Fan is multi-powered and runs on 4 AA batteries or a USB power cord with an AC plug-in adapter. The USB port in on the back of the fan above the battery compartment.The Mainstays On-The-Go Folding Fan has a 3.5 inch diameter blade which is actually fairly quiet and powerful. The USB power cord is 59 inches long which gives you more maneuverability to place the fan where you need it most. The On-The-Go Folding Fan can be taken anywhere. I do not know how long the batteries will last (# of hours on different speeds)but with the USB power cord and a portable/or solar power bank you can have unlimited power. Unfortunately the USB does not charge the batteries. The Mainstays On-the-Go Folding Fan is great as a personal fan, work station fan or for camping, setting on the pic-nic table, using to cool the tent in the evening etc. The On-The-Go Folding Fan is small enough to fit in a purse or backpack yet powerful enough to have 3 speeds. The blue lighted ring around the power button gets brighter with each speed. The Mainstays On the Go Folding fan is extremely portable, but it's the best mini fan I have seen on the market. An awesome Mother's Day/Father's Day gift. Perfect for anyone any day.

title: Great fan for the desk or for traveling
review_text: There's a lot to like about this little fan. I'll start with the positives. First, I love that it can be powered with a USB. This makes it so versatile. With nearly every small device being powered with USB in today's world, that makes this fan able to be powered in the home, vehicles, campers, etc. You could even power it with a portable USB power bank (see pic), making it very travel or camping friendly. Second, you're also able to power it with 4 AA batteries, which makes it versatile (not recommended, see below). Other positives include the portable size, the light weight design, and the stand is adjustable and stiff, meaning, you can alter the angle or direction of the fan. Now the negatives. First, using AA batteries does not last very long. I used AC Delco batteries (not the best, but still good quality batteries), and the fan lasted about 3 hours when on full. Second, there are 3 speeds, however, the first speed seems to hardly move the air. You need your face to be right next to the fan to feel the moving air. I can't really think of many uses for having the fan on the lowest setting. The fan is small enough that you almost always need it on the highest speed to be effective. Overall, I would recommend this fan. If you're a traveler, enjoy camping (in either the tent or camper), or need a little desk fan while you work, this is perfect for you. Just make sure you can power it via the USB rather than AA batteries, otherwise you'll burn through batteries quick.

title: Quick and easy setup
review_text: My neighborhood had a rash of car break ins, so I wanted to get a camera setup to keep an eye on my cars. I like this one, it has easy setup, plug in and it just works. I hooked it up to my TV, and it came right up into configuration screen, answered a few questions and it was up and running. Has a screen where you take a picture with your phone and the app installs real easy. I've only hooked up two cameras of the four that came with it, deciding where to put the other 2. Wires are super long so easy to place where you need.

title: Compact, versatile, and simple to use cctv system!
review_text: It is a wired connection system which is better for stable connection and with 65 feet of wiring, it was plenty enough to set it up where you want. I also like that the power cord is simpler as you only need one to power all the cameras and one to power the DVR so you don't have too many wires with each camera needing it's own power adapter. It's a lot simpler this way. The installation and setup is pretty simple and straightforward and with the preinstalled 1 TB hard drive you have plenty of space to store saved videos. This system comes with 4 cameras but I like that you have the option to add another 4 more if you want. It's compatible with windows, mac, android and iOS so it works with all my devices. The cameras are compact and lightweight so easy to install and fit anywhere. This is a pretty good value home security system that's easy to use and has lots of options so I recommend this to anyone looking for a home/business security system.

title: Nice security camera

review_text: Didn't realize I had to pay a monthly fee to use it. I wouldn't have it if I had been told this.

title: Very happy so far
review_text: Good product, and good seller. very easy to set up and instruction is very clear and helpful. The downloaded app connected with the mini camera quickly and smoothly. and the real-time video was clear too.

title: Great
review_text: The camera is small, very convenient, easy to install, and the picture is very clear. It can be rotated, the quality is also very good, and the price is cheap. Highly recommended

title: Reliable little camera.
review_text: Bought the camera for my family room security. Works great during the nighttime. Great clarity with the picture.

title: Perfect size
review_text: Really nice little camera it work perfect for me better than other I have tried before easy to set up I love it

title: good
review_text: It will be installed in 5 minutes, and the picture is clear. Recently, I gave my son sleep training, which made me feel at ease.

title: The quality is great !
review_text: To watch my dog and to see if someone is stealing out of my bedroom.

title: Works Great!
review_text: Have yet to fully explore this product but I definitely will update my review after I do!

title: Can monitor baby well
review_text: Buy a mini camera and want to monitor the baby's status, just need to buy a memory card!

title: Great Product!
review_text: It is easy to use, and makes me feel safe, like it!

title: Great product
review_text: Takes a little to set up but it is a great product to be using.

title: Reliable Hardware Delivered to My Front Door 1Hr
review_text: I have several WD Externals of various ages, they seem to last a good long time. Not sure if I have had an external fail yet. Works great especially if you have good USB 3.0 or 3.2 ports that can keep up with it and take full advantage of its high speed interface. I have a lot of machines for the work that I do and needed something fast and reliable to transfer a lot of files, store them, and then quickly return them to the server when it was ready after a recent equipment failure. Being able to order one up quickly on Walmart.com and have it brought to my home office in an hour is amazingly convenient and helpful. Where else can you get a 4TB external USB 3.0 HDD at 7:30 at night? Thank you.
My only complaint was the cost a year ago. this item cost half again as much as it does now otherwise it's easy to set up. looks to be quite dependable as most most Western digital items are

title: Great external Hard drive
review_text: I have used WD My Books for over 12 years. Most important when storing files, you want them to be RELIABLE. These are. I've tried Seagate and others as well. Always come back to W. D.

title: Great/Perfect Media Storage at a fair price.
review_text: I am very pleased with my 4TB hard drive. I had worked as a private school teacher for about twenty years, so I had accumulated a great deal of educational materials along the way - including audio courses, an extensive Ebook library, and obviously video and music. The 4TB disk is my storage library - allowing me to retrieve and/or share materials with others at lightning speed - while leaving my 1TB hard disk freed for routine, daily business. I highly recommend this product. And when it fills, buy another and lay it alongside. But most folks would probably not need more than 4TB to store their media.

title: DECADES OF RELIABLE HARD DRIVES
review_text: We started using Western products for business in the late 1980's and had very few quality issues. Later in retirement we continued to use Western external hard drives as backup to our computer drives. In the last decade we began using the external hard drive for all things and no longer relied on the computer hard drive to backup of personal files. We have had only one Western drive unexplained failure some years ago so starting backing up on two or more drives. We still have that drive and when testes after sitting for more than five years it starting operating as if nothing was wrong. Unfortunately it did not last and when shut down would never boot up again. So we still trust in their product after many decades. However we also suggest you backup the backup.

title: Defective, replacement defective too
review_text: Western Digital My Book 12TB external drive would not display in Windows 10 file manager. Ran Western Digital diagnostics and got "SMART status failure". Return unit and purchased another which came with box previously opened. This one did at least have a driver loaded, but still would not display and got "SMART status failure" when running WD diagnostics. I own another WD 12TB drive that has worked fine for years.

title: Run from this!
review_text: Run from this. Regrettably, I bought this one and another 16tb drive because I have the WD Pro and they worked fine. Needed an external usb and bought this brand for the 16tb and 12tb. It has been less than a year and both began making the dreaded click of death!!!! Neither have been replaced yet even though still under warranty. I will never buy WD drives again including the WD Pro (-seriously how would you feel)?

When I got home I noticed the box had already been opened(the seals were broken). I still hooked it to my computer but the hard drive was bad, it was pretty obvious because of the loud ticking noise coming from the disc drive inside enclosure. I had to return to store with hard drive, apparently exchanges are not a thing any more and had to go threw this huge ordeal.

title: Arrived on time as ordered.
review_text: Arrived not working. States "fatal hardware error", after troubleshooting the hard drive is bad. All connections, the cables etc are good and the computer based on trying multiple ports.

title: selling 3 year old computer equipment as new
review_text: When I registered the product with Western Digital, they told me this device was made in Mar 1 2022. My purchase was Mar 15, 2025. They wont honor any warranty until Walmart can prove I was sold a new device and not a used/refurb devise. What a crooked way to do business by selling 3 year old Computer Devices as new. Ever heard of Moores Law? Did you know the generation cycle is normally about 6 months? That would make this drive a Great Great Grandfather. You have shattered my belief and trust I've had in quality of items I get from Walmart

title: Good External Drive
review_text: A large capacity external drive at a reasonable price. I purchased this drive as a second Time Machine backup drive for a Mac Studio Desktop computer. It is not as fast as my primary Thunderbolt drive pro, but I was surprised how much faster it was than my former usb 3 drives were. The power connection is inconsistent with some jiggline of the power plug into the drive, but I can get it to work. And the reasonable price of the refurbished drive is worth the slight power inconvenience.

title: Incompatible with WD Smartware!!!!!
review_text: I was not informed by sales literature or WD website that this drive (part of the new series of drives) is not compatible with WD Smartware Backup software until I looked very deep into their website.. The replacement software (My Backup) will not install on any of my 5 computer systems. It sucks.

title: Terrible
review_text: This USB hard drive is by far the worst one I've ever earned. Every time you try to open a file or you try to save a file it "thinks" for a very long time. It takes so much time to open or close file or just navigating through the folders.

title: Could not be Happier with this purchase!!
review_text: Easy to use and is fast well fast for me anyways have no problem with a big file to transfer to this HD. I do lots of music transfers and this unit is great for me..

title: Reliable & Fast.
review_text: The My Book storage solution has always been a good investment for me. I've been using WD My Book for a long time, and have not had any problems with any of them.

title: Short life. Won't buy WD again.
review_text: Hard drive was great while it worked. Failed a little over a year in. I have multiple hard drives that are pushing 10 years of age. It's a rare occurence for me to have one fail, much less so soon. I won't be purchasing this brand again.

title: Fantastic product
review_text: I am using this as an external hard drive for my PS5. I have a couple hundred games saved on this. The PS4 games run perfectly fine playing off this drive without having to move the game back to the internal drice. I recommend this product.
so far it hasnt failed me yet connected to my ps4 pro so i can have all my ps4 games on my ps5 pro. ive ben transfering sense i got it 5 days ago strait no issues so far.

would have gotten a better review but the cord that connect the hdd to whatever you are using it with was messed up when i got it and they wouldnt replace it somi.had to buy another one. was only 11 bucks but still....not the point.

Definitely a serviceable ssd. if you need more space like i do, this isnt a bad option. I have had mine for 7 or 8 months now and it works as expected. althought the actual size is around 3.6 terabytes due to software space.

title: data is inaccessible after one week
review_text: never set a password but remains locked. Multiple people have the issue and no fix and data is encrypted. If you don't intend on setting a password, don't buy this.
Apps would not get installed on windows 10 PC. Upon connecting it to PC, it would not start and PC froze. I returned it the next day. It seems that the hard drive was damaged.

title: WD My Book external HDD
review_text: The WD My Book external HDD was new/old in the original sealed box. The S/N which is WX72D415388A has a "Ship date" of 11-21-2021, meaning Out-of-Warranty, although new, in the original faded box. I learned this date by calling WD Technical Support. They would not allow me to register the product without an invoice and taking a picture of the sticker on the HDD's bottom.

title: So Far So Good
review_text: I have had a ton of WD drives on both Windows and Mac machines, and, for the most part, they have been great. Too early to tell how this WD 18TB My Book will fair. Recently, I had a 10TB drive fail in a MyBook Duo. Did not last near as long as previous drives. Did not replace the drive. Bought an enclosure for the 2nd drive and using it as a single now. Using the MyBook Duo enclosure as a way to route USB cables. :)

title: Don't Waste Your Time
review_text: When connected to any USB port on front or back of Windows desktop computer, device was recognized by computer, but not by explorer, and therefore it could not be initialized. WIndows reported that most current driver was installed, and that device was working properly. This definitely was not true. I wasted an entire day troubleshooting this item.

title: always get the next size up
review_text: this drive is perfection but next time I will order a larger Drive

title: Good So Far
review_text: Its been a month, not the fastest hard drive but the space and reliability is worth the price

title: A great external device that's easy to use videos
review_text: This works great with downloading videos, and easy to hook up

title: 14tb My Book
review_text: Ok so far?? Time will tell?? Very sad that Western Digital thinks it is unnecessary for a power/active blue LED Light like in the older harddrive??? Don't know it is functioning unless you access from "My PC"?? My old 640Gb had worked great for 18 years. Usb cord is very short?? 3 foot?? How cheap! At least a 6 foot would be acceptable?? Cant even place My Book on desktop?? Won't reach pc tower under desk!! Why??

title: poor quality, bad experience, returned
review_text: the software (.exe file) shipped on drive did not load. The downloaded version had issues. Once I got software up and run the drive made a "clunking" noise every 4 to 5 secs and this was at idle not read or write. Called CS they said this was not normal and to return.

title: I love it - It's the fourth one I have.
review_text: It's sexy on my desk. Reliable, I've never had an issue with anything from WD, and specifically this particular model. My desk and tech are all black, with the charcoal look of my Mac. And it all looks great. I have four of them, as I use one up I buy another to back up the essentials. Each time I buy one it's larger storage and it's great. They stopped supporting an app that came supported on the three I had before this one. It allowed you to change the password and customize how it unlocks when used on your Mac, so that sucks. But the drive itself is fantastic and reliable. Western Digital seems to never disappoint at least not yet.
WD 4tb My Book is best value for what you receive. 4tbs for 100 bucks. The best purchase I've ever made at Walmart.

title: Do not buy. Failed within a week.
review_text: The drive began failing within a week. Not recognized by any system unless forced to mount, endlessly clicking the hours to its demise.

title: Data is secure now
review_text: Greae storage device.provides enormous security in regards to data protectin and recovery. Wish I had it sooner.

title: Great value and portability for off site backup
review_text: Excellent value for off site backup. Can be formatted NTFS or HFS / APFS. Formatted exFAT out of the box.

title: Make sure it has the correct TB's
review_text: When I plugged it in, it only had 10TB's, rather than the 12TB's I ordered %26 per the box label. I had to return it.
It is a great external HD for the price. you can't really beat it. However, its louder than I expected when it is running.

title: DOA
review_text: DOA. Brand spankin new. The computer would see it but when I tried to initialize it it would say fatal hardware error.

title: Trustworthy external hard drive
review_text: This is an excellent external hard drive. It is very dependable and I have owned several of these over the years. It is very important to back up your data and to trust your backup. This 4TB WD My Book is very trustworthy.
Hooked this up to my dish Wally. Formatted without issue, is small enough to fit in my cabinet and gives me a ton of HD storage. Would certainly recommend it.
I have not yet been able to see it under constant usage and I am not sure what will happen when I do. The product loos good, and installed without problem.

title: Reliable HDD - get's the job done 'by the Book'
review_text: Bought a second WD 16TB My Book for my new Mac mini 2024 computer. The first one's still running on my iMac 2017. Easy to use, setup, and run diagnostics

title: Really Efficient , Great Price %26 Unexpected Ft.
review_text: Decently Priced And Perfect Size , Runs really well , also is Energy saving too , if you don't use it for a while in between data backup it goes into a sort of standby mode which was a feature I wasn't expecting but it's Awesome to have!!

title: 12TB - holds everything
review_text: great product - condensing all my externals to this one -- still uses bearings but since it is a backup and not running all the time, acceptable for value.

title: Glad I went with refurb. Good as new!
review_text: Works perfectly! No issues at all. Easily transfers media and runs Plex server.
WD is a good quality product and have always worked well for me.
This manufacturer has a great reputation for quality and reliability.

title: What a shame
review_text: Not sure How this happened but, i bought this hard drive for school and for future work. It didn't work at all. My mac could not find it and my windows was able to find it but the hard drive was corrupted. Could not use it at all.

title: NEVER RECIEVED THE ITEM, SENT TO THE WRONG HOUSE.
review_text: My reason for giving this item a poor rating is because I never received it during that following date whomever delivered it brought it to the wrong house, the only good thing came out of all of this is I contacted customer service, hopefully things will get better.

title: After 1 month, an error occurred
review_text: Installing and formatting was pretty automatic. Starting backups was easy and went well for the first 28 days. Then it stopped backing up and the message was "an error occurred". After running Disk Utility First Aid, it is now running the first back up since the repair, and all seems to be going well. I hope this doesn't happen every month or so.

title: 12TB is Huge But Spinning Drive Is Loud
review_text: This is a great drive if you don't mind a lot of noise and vibration, or if you can keep it far away from your desk. It turned out to be unusable for me, it vibrated my whole desk all day and was quite noisy. I've been spoiled by a completely silent computer since Apple Silicon, I guess I can't use spinning drives any more.

title: WD 18TB My Book Desktop - Very Noisy
review_text: Have had good experiences with WD products in the past. This one is very noisy and constantly making a clicking noise which is very distracting. Not sure if this is normal. I'm concerned that the unit is not functioning properly and will eventually fail when it is out of warranty. Somewhat disappointed with this purchase.

title: Slower than versions with les storage, apparently
review_text: I got the 12tb version and it had a top write speed of 42mbs, even using a USB 3.2 port. I have seen reviews that indicate that the 4tb and 6tb versions have wright speeds of up to 170mbs. Looking through the vents of the chassis it appeared that there was a single disk drive. I think that there was a trade off with size and speed.

title: The unit was manufactured in 2021
review_text: I ordered a 4 TB memory and expect it to at least have its own software included to install. It didn't, so I went out to the manufacturers website to download software. After I did that I found out instead of having a 4 TB I only had a 4.9 MB, now I have to drive into Walmart and get my money back

title: Works with my iMac so far
review_text: I am using this drive as a Time Machine backup device for my iMac. In my case, I formatted the drive to the Apple file system and within minutes after, the drive was creating the first backup on the drive. No issues as of yet. My one complaint is a design flaw by the WD team - a missing power/activity light!!! Get dinged a star for that WD!

title: 4TB My Book Stops working on iMac
review_text: Our 4TB My Book worked well for quite awhile on our iMac desktop. Showed no signs or issues until we were no longer able to access the contents. Fortunately I do have most of the files backed up elsewhere, but would be real nice if this one was still accessible. That way I could be sure of having all of my files. Have replaced this drive with a hopefully higher quality professional model. Stinks that it was out of warranty. this was the first time we have had any problem with WD products.

title: Password safe. Convenient. Trustworthy. Love it.
review_text: I love these. I have two and they work great. I love that I can safely store thousands of files and trust the password feature. Great for storing important documents, family photos, video game storage etc. Ive never had any issues and Ive been using mine for years. First one I bought almost a decade ago and the second one Ive had for a few months. Very convenient and trustworthy.

title: MyBook 4TB external hard driver
review_text: Bought to replace my older (12+ year old) external hard drive. It finally quit.

title: 8 tb
review_text: My largest yet. Plug and off we went, just like the others. Good product!

title: Works Great!
review_text: Tremendous amount of storage! Great Value

title: Works As It Should
review_text: Seems to work as advertised. A bit noisy for a backup drive .
Competitive pricing and delivery was faster than Amazon.

title: I used this hard drive once, then it stopped worki
review_text: I used this hard drive once, then it stopped working.

title: Good Product
review_text: Good product so far it is working for the time being, WD seems to be good product
Easy install, Acronis software worked fine with all my previous drives.

title: Lots of storage
review_text: Great price for such a large capacity external hard drive.

title: Great brand; great product.
review_text: Great brand; great product.
Price was cheaper than other retailers, but WD quality is only middling as similar drive has failed.

title: Solid work horse external hard drive
review_text: The go to hard drive for me when it comes to external storage. western Digital drives are dependable and proven to last.

title: Nice.
review_text: Great and easy! Just backing up files. Found other features confusing and it's all I really need it for anyway.

title: Dead upon opening.
review_text: The external drive did not work; tried multiple outlets to confirm it was not a power issue. Packed it back up and returned it.
Walmart site gives a complete description of what to expect from this PS5. It was delivered on time so I could be home to bring it in the house. And the price was a very fair sale price.

title: This is the EXTERNAL DRIVE you want
review_text: I have around 30 MY BOOK drives. Still one of the best external drives for the price. Seems slower than older models but acceptable. Never had a problem with ANY My BOOK drives quality wise. ALL still work.

title: 1 month in, and very happy üëç
review_text: Bought the 8TB version about a month ago. It made a very slight knocking sound when I first fired it up, but that completely vanished after 15-20 minutes, and it's been quiet since. I ran a full diagnostic, with the included software, just to be sure. I understand that this isn't an SSD, so the speed would not be as fast as my m.2, but I'm still impressed at how quick this little HDD moves. I also love the included software, so you can run the occasional diagnostic scan, and keep your files password protected. I highly recommend this product. üëç

title: Great external storage/space
review_text: I've had an external hardrive before for storing videos, pics, music, etc. (vs. cluttering up my desktop's capacity/space) and this one works like the ones before it----perfectly!! Just plug, play, store!! Only purchased this model cause of the increased capacity/space, but no regrets. So far, so good.

title: Concerning ticking/clicking noises
review_text: Purchased for a system backup. The form factor is nice, and the options to get pretty large drives is great. But, when I powered mine up, I heard these irregular clicking/ticking noises about 1 to 5 seconds apart. It could be that these are just part of the motor moving the drive arm, but the noises persisted even when I wasn't trying to read or write any files. And they sure sounded like the sort of noises that indicate there's a mechanical problem with the drive itself. I found the noises to be pretty annoying, so I returned the drive and will look elsewhere.

title: Works perfectly
review_text: Although my My Book did not come with the easy setup card, I called and was able to get help setting up my new WD Book. I have had my previous WD backup Book for about 10 years, but it was no longer backing up, but definitely got my money's worth on that drive.

title: Cheap unit but stays warm which may fail soon
review_text: Typical WD My book that was nicely priced. What was weird was the funky 2 combined connector... Not sure if this is the new standard USB 3 connector but this was the first time that I see this.... I use this as a backup device and it still stay warm even when it is not backing up. The server that I am backing is configured to turn off the usb interface when not in use. I am not sure if My Book power management is working. May need to switch to a NAS backup if the unit fails prematurely from overheating. Another setup issue that I did not like - I needed to format the unit before using. Would have preferred to have the unit pre-formatted.

title: WD drives work Great
review_text: At first I was going to plug it into my Pr41pro in the usb slot. That worked good on my local network but found out no play back on plex. So I moved it to my usb port on my router. That worked great for more space. I have always had good luck with WD external hard drives. This one works great. I have seven others for many years.

title: Saving important documents
review_text: Great price. I have a 500 gb My book and if I recall I paid $99 for it. The size of this is unbelievable!! Transfering my dad's purple heart, and rescue from his Tokyo Raiders days along with the news articles in the World Telegraph. The originals are deteriorating.

Overall, everything was really good. The only problem is that the WalMart online website very often does not provide enough information about the products they sell. For example, there was no information about what computer operating systems were compatible with this product. I did not discover that information until I opened the product box and read the info sheet. I've encountered this problem with a lot of WalMart online products. This has, on several occasions, prompted me to purchase the product from other stores that provided full information about the product. It would seem to me that it would be easy to include that info if the person uploading the product on the WalMart website simply pretended to be the prospective buyer and asked themselves what info they would need to know before deciding to buy the product. I know there are buyers in the real world that can come up with some strange questions. But most buyers know what info about a product they need.

title: Pleased with my purchase
review_text: I'm very pleased with the purchase of My Book Desktop Hard Drive. I was looking for a backup drive so I would not lose my files again after having lost some very important files before the purchase. I have an older laptop so I'm not sure if it's the laptop or the hard drive but it seems that when I leave My Book attached to my laptop the laptop will not complete the startup cycle until I disconnect the external hard drive. I can then reconnect it once it has completed the startup. This makes it difficult to schedule routine backups but I am overall pleased that I actually have an external hard drive with enough space to hold as much info as I will ever put on it.

title: Satisfied
review_text: Even with a Mac, a plug and play. Works flawlessly. Second WD drive I have bought. Only reason why I bought it is the first one is older than Moses, and started not working reliably, and it is not supported by WD any longer. I am confident this one too will last a long time with faithful service.

title: Why i purchased 2- 18 TB WD My Book Ext. drives
review_text: If you are going to use this device with a Mac, you (may) need to contact WD technical support to guide you through reformatting prior to use. The reformatting process is logical, but can not be installed using the internal Mac disc utilities, you will need to install WD's download and use tech support to help make this a quick and easy process. This device, ( of which i purchased two) an 18TB My Book, will be used here as back up to my 48TB G Raid 4 bay Shuttle. I do not use the cloud for storage and would prefer to house my own back up. My digital life began with an ever increasing number of By Book's in the 1990's, and then migrated everything to G Drive storage. What I have done now, in this purchase is consolidate 12 G drives into, 1 48 TB G 4bay shuttle and 2- 18 TB My Book drives to bring of my storage needs up to date, with space available for adding data for a few years to come. This series of recent purchases represents my continued loyalty and trust in the performance reliability of products from WD for well over two decades.

title: Good value at Walmart
review_text: This external hard drive is highly rated and reviewed on the internet when used as a backup device. People who use it for other purposes than backup do not seem to like it. However, for my purposes it is perfect and the Walmart price was the best on the web. I have used WD products for years and always been satisfied. My single complaint is the setup. No instructions in the box, nothing happened when I plugged it in. Thankfully YouTube has some excellent videos on how to setup and by going to the WD website I found the software needed to get the job done; although not all of it is there. WD sent me to the Acronis website for a free download on their software made for the WD hard drive. This is not a process for those who do not have some experience setting up computer equipment. But for those with moderate experience the job was straight forward and I was able to easily backup my computer which is why I bought this hard drive. I recommend as described above.

title: Driver problems
review_text: This 4tb WD and a WD 1tb are the only ones out of 8 external hard drive that had any problems loading the drivers. Cheaper unknown brands gave me no problems at start up, except WD brand. I was able to get the drivers to final load on the 1tb but this 4tb only 2 of the 3 drivers would load. I don't know that I can trust it. This is my 1st 4tb. Others are 500gb to 2tb. Only this 4tb requires to be plugged into an outlet to work at all. Won't get its power from laptop. Hadn't realized that but maybe that is just because of being my 1st 4tb. While I'll keep it and see how it works, I hate returning, No more WD brand for me! The deal breaker is the difficulty right from the start with its inability to load the drivers, which not even the cheapest other brands had any problems.

title: Great buy!
review_text: I bought it for backing up my laptop. Good price. And I was able to upload all my files/data from Windows 7, 64bit even though the information sheet said it was compatible with only Windows 10 . And only 2 days shipping for free. Great buy. I am going to purchase 2 more so I'll have enough sequential back-up capability.

title: Works, but missing the activity light
review_text: It works, but I really miss the activity light on my other external drives that Western Digital used to put on the My Book drives. My other complaint is that the utilities that came with it are not backward compatable with my old My Book drives and made them inoperable.

title: My Book 8TB (owned 3 wks)
review_text: Quick shipping. Worked immediately after plugging in. I was concerned that I couldn't use it to backup a system image (windows 10), but discovered that this was because it wasn't formatted with NTFS. After reformatting, it worked fine. I decided to use bitlocker for encryption instead of the WD software, for ease/transparency of use with windows 10. My only small annoyance so far is that the drive seems to spin down after only a few minutes of non-use. This means that accessing it periodically (on the order of minutes) takes more time because it needs to spin up again each time. I bought it to replace a seagate drive which died only shortly out of warranty. I hope this drive shows itself to be more reliable.

title: Works But Loud
review_text: My second unit after the first no longer worked with my Apple operating system. Used the first now and then with Time Machine and it worked fine. Haven't used the second yet. Only down side is the noise the second makes sitting on my desk which "microphones" the sound. Had to bungee cord it to a slab of cork and then set the slab on an air cushion to dampen the WD unit's loud vibes.

title: Too Many Pictures!
review_text: My desktop says that I have too many pictures cramping my "storage", so I went looking for external storage. Purchased MY BOOK after reading another reviewer with the same storage problem with is pictures. Seems easy enough to use and has plenty of room. 1 Tb should be plenty of room for my pictures and music files!

title: Damaged
review_text: When I first hooked this up it had a really bad vibration and was super loud when reading/writing files. Also had like a bad rhythmic vibration that you can hear and feel just by touching my desk it was on. Few days later it stopped showing up in my files. I had to unplug and plug in the power every now and then for it to show up. So now I am re-transferring my data to the old drive and replacing this with another brand.

title: Easy To Use.
review_text: Easy to use. Attached to PC running Windows 10 and was quickly detected and added to file system. Been adding 1800+ DVD/Blu-Ray movie collection to the drive and data transfer speed has been quite good. Have only had for a couple of weeks so can't say much about the longevity of the unit. Only time will tell ;-).

title: Tons of Capacity and Speed!
review_text: Super Quick! Our biggest Bottleneck was older HDDs thats couldn't handle the throughput. It's a perfect Archive drive or daily backups. We reformatted it though before use which over a day, which is no big deal, but it gave us an extra 800GB of storage which was a major plus for us. But if you are not familiar with formatting don't go doing that. Anyways 10/10 I will get again for more archive files.

title: Problems with the drive I received (12 TB My Book)
review_text: Unfortunately the drive I received here is a bum. From day one, it made loud grinding noises. My other drives do not make these noises. When I checked the drive, it didn't show errors so I checked the cords with alternatives I knew to be working well. The noise was not consistent so I attempted to load files. The files wouldn't show correctly as if they weren't loading onto the drive. When I closed the folder and reopened, they were there. This is also not normal behavior. I also noticed intermittent behaviors were the drive would load much slower than the rest (including another 12 tb with matching files). Sometimes taking 15-20 minutes (I'd give up on it loading and go do something else only to come back and it's loaded). It has caused disk utility to crash and I haven't had that happen before. DU only crashes or loads very slowly when this drive is connected. Sometimes the drive doesn't connect at all. I reached out for support but will likely have to exchange under warranty. I feel there is something not right and I have numerous WD EHD's, this one is not behaving normally. I have a concern of being forced into a refurbished option but my drive is only 2.5 months old and has had this problem since day one. I wish I'd gone with my gut for the exchange before the first 30 days. I am also concerned I will now have additional shipping costs despite that this drive was sent to me like this.

title: Watch out for drive swaps!!!
review_text: I went to my local Walmart yesterday and bought 2 of these 8TB drives to shuck for my NAS (remove the drive from the enclosure to install into a computer). The first drive opened with no problem and it had a white label 8TB drive inside. Installed in NAS and works beautifully. The second drive, however, would not open. One side was stuck and wouldn't budge. Since I had no plan to use the enclosure and only wanted the drive inside, I went ahead and used a screwdriver to forcibly crack open the enclosure to get to the drive. I was shocked/angered to see that it had a 320GB drive inside, not the 8TB drive it should have. Someone took out the 8TB drive and replaced it with a cheap 320GB drive. How it ended up back in the case with the others, available to sell with 2 uncut security labels I had to cut to open the box is beyond me. It almost makes me think it was an employee that did it. They had also glued one side of the enclosure tray which is why I couldn't open it. I was able to get a refund, but just wanted to give everyone a heads up that people are doing this and that even though the case appears to be new and unopened, that may not be the case.

title: 1 Big Flaw, but Good for the Price
review_text: I bought this product because i needed more storage on my computer, but i plan to upgrade in a few months due to Windows 10 end of support on an already aging computer, because buying a interal ssd to fit my exact motherboard wasn't worth it for only a short time. Overall, I've found the onn external SSD to be a mixed bag. The presentation was great when i opened the box. The drive came in a carrying case with 2 cables. The speeds, while not the fastest, exceeded expectations, and it is miles ahead of my old early 2000s HHD. It's lightweight and easy to carry if you want the same offline storage on your work and home computer. That all being said, it's got 1 big drawback, that being a huge discrepancy in storage capacity. It's listed as a 500GB drive, but mine only has 466GB. Normally, a slight discrepancy is common in budget storage devices sold today, maybe by a few GB or maybe 10 or 15 at worst, but a discrepancy of 34GB that's a lot of missing storage.
so far seems great, i apparently have a bug from some old thing that says it is 9 gig but in reality its just 14, but thats my problem to figure out, the product works well...
Did not know it would not work on tv usb port because of Xfat file system instead of fat 32 but can still be useful as another backup for all my files. Always something to learn you didn't know.

title: Plenty of storage
review_text: Let me start off by saying this SSD drive is the perfect size to take anywhere. You can put it in your center console in your car, your purse, and keep it in your computer desk with plenty of extra room. I was able to transfer all my photos/videos to the SSD drive from my laptop and still have plenty of room left over for future images. Then I copied everything to my PC with the USB cable provided with the kit. I can store so many files on the drive it's amazing, and the dive is small enough to fit in my hand. I highly recommend this product especially if you work from home, in any field working with computers, or just need extra storage you can take anywhere. It's sleek design, two USB cables, and heavy duty, but light case are an added bonus.

title: Very convenient storage device
review_text: This hard drive itself is very lightweight and slim as well as visually appealing. There is a. Hole that you could hook the hard tube on to something to make travel easier. There is 2 included cables for it. 1 usb c to usb c and the other usb a to usb a for those computer and devices that may not have a usb c port. I'm glad that was thought of. This all comes in a hard cover protective zip up case with 2 mesh pockets on the inside that will keep your hard drive and cord secure. Everything especially the case is good quality. Very happy with this.

title: So much storage for such a small device
review_text: I was pleasantly surprised at how much could fit on this. I recently broke the screen on my laptop amd needed to get files off of it quickly. I was able to hook up a monitor and use this to move files and pictures over to my spare. It is easy to use and so portable. Highly recommend.

title: A dream to use if you travel often!
review_text: Quick, easy, and super lightweight- this little hard drive does the job! Easily recognized on my PC, and moved items like photos and movies lightning fast. I also appreciated the extra double usbC sided cord, which makes moving around hundreds of photos from my phone even easier. It's super lightweight design makes it pocket/purse friendly as well, with a little hole for a keychain. It also comes with an easily packable hard case if you prefer a little protection. All in all, a great little product if you're looking for storage on the go.

title: Perfect for photos and video!!!

title: Good backup SSD
review_text: This is a good backup solid state drive. It is fast as it is advertised. It also has much more capicity than a typical USB thumb drive. The capcity of the 250G gives it a lot of room for files (ppt, videos, pictures). I tested it with using it as a portable game drive. While it would only hold 1-3 of the larger games, it does do a good job at holding smaller games. The response time loading from it is also good. For the curret cost it is well worth it.

title: Fast speed
review_text: I was sent this Keep onn. Ultra fast portable solid-state drive 259 GB to test out complimentary in exchange for my honest and unbiased opinion. First off I love that is comes with its own travel carrying case and two cords, one that is a usb to usb-c and the other being usb-c to usb-c, great for on the go. It's ultra lightweight, I did notice that the material on the sides felt somewhat squishy when you squeezed it so I would be cautious with it not to accidentally put anything heavy on it and to keep it in the carrying case at all times when not in use. Fast transfer speed, it connected to my husbands android galaxy s22 phone right away with you no issues, however my iPhone 14 pro max I could not get it to connect to. When attempting to connect it to my computer I had to run a windows update before the drive was recognized, initially said not enough power to use drive - worked fine after windows update and restart.

title: Small yet large storage external drive
review_text: It is super easy to set up, plug in and format. It holds a ton for it's compact size making it easy to carry around all the data you need without having to have a laptop or desktop. You can use it to back up your files so you have something to fall back on if you lose the original!

title: Small and fast!
review_text: I received the 500GB version. The plastic housing feels cheap, which is one of the two things I don't like about it so far. It's really light, which is great. As long as the plastic housing can handle being in a backpack, etc it should be good. This unit is fast, which is fabulous. I haven't tried moving videos yet, but I did move an entire folder filled with graphic design assets and it moved it easily in under a minute. Felt like seconds. The other thing I don't like is the 500GB size. We need terabytes of storage today, so this is much too small. But when they make the terabyte sizes, I say buy one asap. Until then only buy if you need this small amount of back up or added storage space. Thank you for allowing me to test and review this for you onn. and Home Tester Club, it's a great find.

title: 1 Big Flaw, but Good for the Price
review_text: I bought this product because i needed more storage on my computer, but i plan to upgrade in a few months due to Windows 10 end of support on an already aging computer, because buying a interal ssd to fit my exact motherboard wasn't worth it for only a short time. Overall, I've found the onn external SSD to be a mixed bag. The presentation was great when i opened the box. The drive came in a carrying case with 2 cables. The speeds, while not the fastest, exceeded expectations, and it is miles ahead of my old early 2000s HHD. It's lightweight and easy to carry if you want the same offline storage on your work and home computer. That all being said, it's got 1 big drawback, that being a huge discrepancy in storage capacity. It's listed as a 500GB drive, but mine only has 466GB. Normally, a slight discrepancy is common in budget storage devices sold today, maybe by a few GB or maybe 10 or 15 at worst, but a discrepancy of 34GB that's a lot of missing storage.

I haven't tried moving videos yet, but I did move an entire folder filled with graphic design assets and it moved it easily in under a minute. Felt like seconds. The other thing I don't like is the 500GB size. We need terabytes of storage today, so this is much too small. But when they make the terabyte sizes, I say buy one asap. Do you research do you research on the vendor the person selling it the reviews the specs, everything thank you God bless each and every person reading this.

title: A few features not working as expected
review_text: The CX3 was easy to set up, has a nice large screen (maybe a bit too big for my wrist) and band was a good size for a smaller wrist. For the most part, steps, heart rate, miles are in synch with other tracking apps/watches I am using. I do not like that on the watch, the calories burned are fraction of what my previous watch recorded (e.g. One-hour of yoga my previous watch showed around 250 kcal, this watch recorded 6 kcal) . Also, When I select outdoor walk on the watch, it does not open the walk tracking on the app on my phone and vice versa (again, about 30 minutes walking on watch recorded 66 kcal, app on phone 145 kcal). I also did not receive a verbal notification or vibration when I hit 1-mile as I do on my previous watch. The manual and website do not address these issues. title: CX3 Smart Watch: Sleek, Advanced, and Affordable
review_text: I recently bought the CX3 Smart Watch, and I have to admit, I‚Äôm blown away by how advanced it is. It honestly reminds me of an Apple Watch but at a fraction of the price‚Äîand in some ways, it‚Äôs even better. The design is sleek, lightweight, and modern, and the display is bright and easy to read. Setting it up was super simple, and the connection to my phone through the Runmifit app was seamless. What really stands out is the Bluetooth calling feature‚Äîit works flawlessly, and the sound quality is surprisingly good for a smartwatch in this price range. The fitness tracking is accurate and covers all the basics like steps, heart rate, and calories, which is exactly what I need. The battery life is solid too. I get about two days of use, which is more than I expected given all the features it offers. Overall, this watch completely exceeded my expectations. It looks and feels high-end, performs like a much more expensive smartwatch, and is packed with features. If you‚Äôre on the fence about getting it, don‚Äôt hesitate‚Äîyou won‚Äôt be disappointed. title: Not too fancy. But it's just right for me!
review_text: Since this is my first smart watch my expectations are not high. It's easy to understand and maneuver through all the options. I was concerned about the battery life. It was dying pretty fast. However, I accidentally figured out how to save the battery life by A LOT! Bring up your list of options. Select Phone Call (turn off). Go back and select Settings ‚Äê Display - Turn on Wrist Raise (This lights up your watch every time you raise your arm/ wrist). I waited a few minutes, and then turned it off. My battery has been just below full for two days so far. Reducing the vibration or putting it on mute also provides better measurements. Actually, anything I'm not using is turned off until I need it. My only disappointment is the sleep tracker does not give a Last Seven Day Report unless I view it directly in the app. The rotating bezel is a huge plus for my fat fingers. The most valuable feature is the Find Phone. Misplacing my phone occurs many times throughout the day. Don't worry if your phone is on mute. It will continue to vibrate until you find it. Off mute, it sounds off pretty loud. Along with other shortcuts, and decent set of workout videos provided by the app, this was money well spent! I hope this helps.

title: Quality microphone!
review_text: I am actually a bit surprised by the quality of this USB microphone. I was expecting something lighter, maybe made of plastic, but this is a solid, microphone with a good amount of weight in the metal base. Having this kind of weight allows it to sit on a desk or table without being easily knocked over. Package comes with one microphone, a USB cord, and instructions. The mic, itself, has a headphone jack and USB-C port, and then also includes a 1/4" threaded hole for mounting to a stand. The great thing about this mic is how simple it is to use-- You just plug in and play. It's compatible with Windows, Mac, and Chromebook. Quality of the sound and recording is decent, and the mic has the ability to make cardioid and omnidirectional recording patterns too! Great microphone for recording professional podcasts, vlogs, videos, and voice-overs for gaming!

title: Great Beginner Studio Mic
review_text: There was a time a few years ago when the computer mounted microphone was sufficient. Times have changed. I needed an external mic that is able to capture natural sound. Came across this onn. microphone and wanted to give it a try. I got to say I am not disappointed. The clarity is far superior to other USB mics that I have used and light years ahead of the internal PC microphone. I tested the internal against this onn and the results are immediately obvious. Much crisper frequency response on the onn. While the body of the microphone is plastic the unit does have nice weight to it. The plastic construction does not detract from my opinion. It has all the features and functions of a much more expensive microphone. It's got a nice gunmetal gray finish that goes perfectly with any PC. I wasn't expecting much considering the price and I've got to say I am pleasantly surprised! Same quality and function as a much more expensive unit. If you need a studio mic, give this one a try!

title: Great for beginners
review_text: So this is a decent microphone for the price point. It was really easy to set up and use. I also like all of the different options that I can do. review_text: My 14 year old loves singing and desperately wanted to record herself to post on social media for her family to watch and this microphone has made it possible!
